function maxSegSumAfterQueries(nums, removeQueries) {
    const n = nums.length;
    const answer = new Array(n);
    const removed = new Set([-1, n]);

    let currentSum = 0, maxSum = 0;
    for (const x of nums) {
        if (x > 0) currentSum += x;
        else {
            maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, currentSum);
            currentSum = 0;
        }
    }
    maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, currentSum);

    for (let i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        const removeIdx = removeQueries[i];
        answer[i] = maxSum;
        nums[removeIdx] = -nums[removeIdx];

        const leftIdx = Math.max(...removed).filter(x => x < removeIdx);
        const rightIdx = Math.min(...removed).filter(x => x > removeIdx);

        let leftSum = 0, rightSum = 0;
        for (let j = rightIdx - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
            if (nums[j] < 0) leftSum -= nums[j];
            else break;
        }
        for (let j = leftIdx + 1; j < n; ++j) {
            if (nums[j] < 0) rightSum -= nums[j];
            else break;
        }

        maxSum -= Math.max(0, leftSum - (-nums[removeIdx]));
        maxSum -= Math.max(0, rightSum - (-nums[removeIdx]));
        maxSum += Math.max(0, leftSum + rightSum - (-nums[removeIdx]));

        removed.add(removeIdx);
    }

    return answer;
}
```    
    1. Create an auxiliary set `removed` to store the indices of removed elements, and initialize it with indices `-1` and `n`. These indices will be used to indicate the left and right boundaries of segments.

2. Calculate the initial maximum segment sum `maxSum` by iterating through the given `nums`.

3. Iterate through the `removeQueries` array. For each removal query:

   a. Store the current `maxSum` value in the answer array.

   b. Update the value of `nums[removeIdx]` to its negation.

   c. Determine the left and right boundaries of the segments connected to the removed element.

   d. Calculate the sums of the elements in the connected segments.

   e. Update the `maxSum` value by subtracting the segment sums connected to the removed element and adding back the sum of the modified segment after the removal.

   f. Add the index of the removed element to the `removed` set.

4. Return the answer array.

